description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a highly motivated and enthusiastic individual to join the Ophthalmology administration team. You will need to provide an efficient and comprehensive secretarial service and should have previous medical secretarial and administrative experience. Excellent organisational skills are required as is the ability to work under pressure, prioritise workloads and work to deadlines. You will be required to monitor the Trust RADAR system on a daily basis to ensure all patients that you are dealing with are moved along their RTT pathway in a timely fashion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent communication skills are required and the post holder will need to have the ability to liaise with staff at all levels and work effectively and efficiently as part of a team. This is a busy role and the post holder will need to have a flexible approach to work and be able to use their own initiative.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is a full time post working 37.5 hours per week over 5 days.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Laura Winters - Interim Clinical Admin Lead on Tel: 07407398942. Or email: laurawinters@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
